  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the low sequencing coverage of these ARGs likely impeded their assembly into larger contigs, explaining why they were not detected in the assemblies (Yorki et al., 2023).",
    "For example, detection of oqxB but not oqxA in sample A reads could indicate incomplete coverage of the oqxB surroundings, as these normally form a single operon (Li et al., 2019).",
    "In contrast, FQ ARGs retrieved by both read-and assemblybased approaches were found at higher read counts than those exclusively observed in reads.",
    "For example, in the case of oqxAB in sample B, both analysis methods corresponded, and identified K. pneumoniae as the host.",
    "In sample A however, read-based ARGhost linking attributed the qnrS1 gene to multiple host replicons, while it was unambiguously situated on a single plasmid in the metagenomic assembly."
  ],
